Finally, the solar irradiance consists of massless photons with energy. When these photons interact with PCs solar umbrella, they will be absorbed, and then they will be converted to thermal energy. Thus, the thermal energy has been calculated by the following: Firstly, by calculating the absorption power, this power is converted to kinetic energy, and this kinetic energy is considered as the thermal energy. The boundary conditions of the simulation procedure for the acrylic tank filled with saline water (which discuss in the next part) to estimate the thermal losses are: convection on all side walls equal to 5 W/m2 K, radiation from all side walls and water surface with emissivity equal to 0.95, and the initial temperature of water adjusted to be 20 °C. Also, the meshing size must be 10 times smaller than the smallest incident wavelength to get more accurate results in the finite element method as we discuss in our previous work at48. The simulation meshing parameters are the maximum element size equal to 3×10-9(m)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
