Here, we choose a good absorber and a good emitter material. Consequently, the designed porous structures of titanium nitrate (TiN) coated with titanium dioxide (TiO2) are a good candidate for the thermal desalination process due to their excellent optical and thermal properties, which have been discussed previously in the last paper48. TiN/TiO2 floats on the saline water surface also. It can absorb up to 90% of the incident solar spectrum. In Fig. 8, we have shown the thermal energy distribution for the saline water and one-dimensional PCs from TiN/TiO2 for one-period above.Figure 8
